 {"id":"agentic_coding_flywheel_setup-pom","title":"Implement ACFS self-update","description":"## What
Before updating other components, acfs-update should update itself:
1. git pull in ~/.acfs (or wherever ACFS is installed)
2. Re-source the update script if it changed
3. Continue with other updates using latest logic

## Why This Matters
- Ensures we have the latest update logic before updating tools
- Fixes any bugs in the update process itself
- Keeps checksums.yaml current (though not used for updates)

## Technical Details
- ACFS installed at ~/.acfs or detected via ACFS_HOME env var
- git pull --ff-only to avoid merge conflicts
- If update script changed, need to re-exec with same args

## Considerations
- What if git pull fails? (network, conflicts)
- Should we require this, or make it optional?
- Re-exec is tricky - need to preserve all args and state

## Decision
Make self-update automatic but non-fatal. If it fails, warn and continue with current version.

## Success Criteria
- [ ] ACFS self-updates on each run
- [ ] Handles git pull failures gracefully
- [ ] Re-exec works if script changed (or skip re-exec v1)","status":"closed","priority":2,"issue_type":"task","created_at":"2025-12-21T13:26:45.271437-05:00","updated_at":"2025-12-21T13:31:43.349328-05:00","closed_at":"2025-12-21T13:31:43.349328-05:00","close_reason":"Out of scope for v1. ACFS is not git-cloned to ~/.acfs, so self-update requires re-running the installer. Users can do this manually. Consider for v2 after changing install to use git clone.","dependencies":[{"issue_id":"agentic_coding_flywheel_setup-pom","depends_on_id":"agentic_coding_flywheel_setup-75e","type":"blocks","created_at":"2025-12-21T13:27:25.670496-05:00","created_by":"daemon"}]}
 {"id":"agentic_coding_flywheel_setup-pu11","title":"Fix CAAM 'list' to 'ls' in safety-tools-lesson.tsx","description":"BACKGROUND
==========
During deep-dive analysis of the CAAM source code and README, discovered that the safety-tools-lesson.tsx uses 'caam list' but the correct command is 'caam ls'.

SOURCE VERIFICATION
===================
From /tmp/dicklesworthstone_tools/caam/README.md line 210:
  | caam ls [tool] | List all saved profiles in vault |

From CAAM CLI source code (no 'list' subcommand defined - 'ls' is the command).

The README Quick Start section (line 193-196) also shows:
  $ caam ls claude
  alice@gmail.com
  bob@gmail.com
  carol@gmail.com

ISSUE LOCATIONS
===============
1. Line 229: Command list shows 'caam list [tool]'
   Should be: 'caam ls [tool]'

2. Line 344: Quick Reference shows 'caam list [tool]'
   Should be: 'caam ls [tool]'

FIX
===
Replace 'caam list' with 'caam ls' in both locations.

REASONING
=========
- 'ls' is the canonical command per CAAM README and source code
- 'list' is NOT a valid CAAM command (will error if user tries it)
- Lesson content must match official tool documentation to avoid confusion

TESTING
=======
After fix, verify commands match CAAM README section 'Command Reference > Auth File Swapping'","status":"closed","priority":1,"issue_type":"bug","created_at":"2025-12-25T18:00:17.38573-05:00","updated_at":"2025-12-25T18:01:00.475866-05:00","closed_at":"2025-12-25T18:01:00.475866-05:00","close_reason":"Fixed 'caam list' to 'caam ls' in both command list (line 229) and quick reference (line 345)","dependencies":[{"issue_id":"agentic_coding_flywheel_setup-pu11","depends_on_id":"agentic_coding_flywheel_setup-lyf0","type":"blocks","created_at":"2025-12-25T18:00:24.093155-05:00","created_by":"daemon"}]}
